    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PN211">
<l>añcuvaru marapiṉ veñciṉam puyalē</l>
<l>ṟaṇaṅkuṭai yaravi ṉaruntalai tumiya</l>
<l>niṉṟukāṇ paṉṉa nīṇmalai miḷirak</l>
<l>kuṉṟutū veṟiyu maravam pōla</l>
<l>muraceḻun tiraṅkun tāṉaiyoṭu talaicceṉ</l>
<l>ṟaraicupaṭak kaṭakku muraicā ṟōṉṟaṉiṉ</l>
<l>ṉuḷḷi vanta vōṅkunilaip paricileṉ</l>
<l>vaḷḷiyai yātaliṉ vaṇaṅkuva ṉivaṉeṉak</l>
<l>koḷḷā māntar koṭumai kūṟaniṉ</l>
<l>ṉuḷḷiyatu muṭittōy maṉṟa muṉṉāṭ</l>
<l>kaiyuḷ ḷatupōṟ kāṭṭi vaḻināṭ</l>
<l>poyyoṭu niṉṟa puṟanilai varutta</l>
<l>nāṇā yāyiṉu nāṇak kūṟiye</l>
<l>ṉuṇaṅku cennā vaṇaṅka vēttip</l>
<l>pāṭap pāṭap pāṭupukaḻ koṇṭaniṉ</l>
<l>ṉāṭukoḷ viyaṉmārpu toḻutaṉeṉ paḻiccic</l>
<l>celva lattai yāṉē vaikalum</l>
<l>valci yiṉmaiyiṉ vayiṉvayiṉ māṟi</l>
<l>yilleli maṭinta tolcuvar varaippiṟ</l>
<l>pāa liṉmaiyiṟ palpāṭu cuvaittu</l>
<l>mulaikkōṇ maṟanta putalvaṉoṭu</l>
<l>maṉaittolain tiruntaveṉ vāṇutaṟ paṭarntē.</l>
</lg>
<lg xml:lang="en">
<l corresp="6">O appearance worthy of words who wins, so that kings fall, </l>
<l corresp="5">when going at the head of [your] army where drums rise [and] sound </l>
<l corresp="4">similar to the sound that widely attacks the hills </l>
<l corresp="3">so that tall mountains roll over as if one had seen [them] standing, </l>
<l corresp="2">so that the heads difficult [to approach] of frightful snakes are cut off, </l>
<l corresp="1">[the sound] of hot angry thunder claps in the rain, according to fearful custom, </l>
<l corresp="6">I am a gift-seeker of high standing who has come remembering you. </l>
<l corresp="9">While people who do not understand talk cruelty </l>
<l corresp="8">“because you are generous this one will bow”, </l>
<l corresp="10a-c">you have finalised your thinking indeed. </l>
<l corresp="10d-11c">As on a former day you showed [your] hand as if something was inside it, </l>
<l>on the following, day even though you are not ashamed (11d+13ab)</l>
<l corresp="12">of [my] suffering in standing outside where I stand with [your] falsehood </l>
<l corresp="13cd">  [I], having talked so that [you] would be ashamed, </l>
<l corresp="14">having praised so that my subtle refined tongue is tormented, </l>
<l corresp="16">having adored as one who worships the murderous wide chest </l>
<l corresp="15">of you who take the praise of [my] singing, while singing [and] singing, </l>
<l corresp="17a-c">I will go, </l>
<l corresp="22">– setting our for my [girl with] bright forehead who sits forelorn in the house </l>
<l corresp="21">with a son who has forgotten to take the breast </l>
<l corresp="20">after having tasted many times the absence of milk, </l>
<l corresp="19">within the bounds of ancient walls where the house rats droop, </l>
<l>changing from side to side in the absence of food daily. (17f-18)</l>
</lg>
